ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: SKIP_SU INTERVIEWER: Skip section SU?
SU1 Now I am going to ask you some (further) questions aboutSUicide. Have you ever thought about killing yourself?
SU1a (Earlier you told me that you thought about taking your own life) Did those thoughts persist for at least 7 days in a row?
SU1b Did you have a plan? (Did you actually consider a way to take your life?)
SU_ao1 How old were you the very first time you had these thoughts about taking your own life?
SU_ar1 How old were you when you last had these thoughts about taking your own life?
SU_r1 Did you have these thoughts within the last 30 days?
SU2 Have you ever tried to kill yourself?
SU2a (Earlier you said that you tried to kill yourself) How many times (did you try to kill yourself)?
SU_ao2 How old were you the very first time (you tried to kill yourself)?
SU_o2 (You tried to kill yourself) Was this within the last 30 days?
SU_ar2 How old were you the last time (you tried to kill yourself)?
SU_r2 Was this within the last 30 days?
SU3 How did you try to kill yourself? IF MORE THAN 1, ASK ABOUT THE MOST SERIOUS ATTEMPT. CODE SILENTLY: TYPE OF METHOD INTENDED
Notes: 1=Fire gun;2=Crash car;3=Carbon monoxide poisoning;4=Cut wrists or stab self;5=Take pills;6=Jump from height;7=Jump in front of train/car/vehicle;8=Strangulation, choking, suffocation, hanging, drowning;9=Other or combination; -8=DK AND REFUSAL

ElementDescription: SU3a How close did you come to killing yourself? CODE SILENTLY: DEGREE OF COMPLETION.
Notes: 2=Put self in vicinity (e.g., brought gun/pills into room, walked into train station);3=Stopped short of completing act (held gun/pills, stood on edge of platform, sat in car);4=Attempted act (jumped, pulled trigger, swallowed pills); -8=DK AND REFUSAL

ElementDescription: SU3b Did you really want to die?
SU3c  CODE SILENTLY: INTENT
Notes: 1=Unclear (no information or not sure);2=Denies intent;3=Reports minimal intent;4=Reports significant intent with some ambivalence;5=Very severe/extreme intent to die; -8=DK AND REFUSAL

ElementDescription: SU3d Afterwards, were you sorry that you didn't die?
SU4 How old were you then?
SU5 Did you require medical treatment after you tried to kill yourself?
SU6 Were you admitted to a hospital after the attempt (for medical reasons)?
SU6a Were you admitted to a hospital after the attempt for psychiatric reasons?
SU6b Did you see a doctor or counselor because you (thought about killing yourself/made a plan to kill yourself/tried to kill yourself)?
SU8 Did you think you would die from what you had done?
SU9.1 Did you try to kill yourself: ...while feeling depressed?
SU9.2 (Did you try to kill yourself:) ...while feeling extremely good or high?
SU9.3 (Did you try to kill yourself:) ...after you had been drinking?
SU9.4 (Did you try to kill yourself:) ...after using drugs?
SU9.5 (Did you try to kill yourself:) ...while having strange thoughts or experiences, or while seeing visions?
SU9.6 (Did you try to kill yourself:) ...under other circumstances?
SU12 (Other than when you tried to take your own life,) did you ever hurt yourself on purpose, for example, by cutting or burning yourself?
SU12a How many times?
SU_ao12 How old were you the first time (you tried to hurt yourself on purpose)?
SU_o12 Was it within the last 30 days?
SU_ar12 How old were you the last time (you tried to hurt yourself on purpose)?
SU_r12 Was it within the last 30 days?
